    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a 4-level hierarchical structure with mixed data types: nominal categorical (location types), ordinal (vehicle categories), and ratio-scale quantitative values (fatality counts). Original data from the IIHS maintains domain validity with appropriate value ranges (\u03bc=2,857, \u03c3=2,346 across leaf nodes). The sunburst visualization maximizes data-ink ratio by using angular spans for quantities and color brightness for hierarchy depth, following Tufte's principles. Cairo's perceptual taxonomy is addressed through: 1) Hue differentiation for urban/rural dichotomy 2) Luminance variations encoding subcategory levels 3) Proportional sectors enabling magnitude comparisons. Statistical coherence is maintained through exact parent-child value summation (\u2211 Rural = 16,512, \u2211 Urban = 23,602) and realistic transportation mortality distributions (70% vehicles vs 30% vulnerable road users)."
